The paper deals with the application of nonbinary low-density parity-check (NB-LDPC) codes to binary input inter-symbol interference (ISI) channels, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed algorithms involve joint detection and decoding, which is a common theme in signal processing (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of the algorithms, which is a topic related to computer communications (cs.CC).
